DIV1.P:
FAMILY attachments have this advantage over all others, that they are not subject to satiety. Parental fondness is augmented by the growth and expansion of every charm and merit in a child; and as it naturally happens that the pa∣rents begin to decline when the children have arrived at their zenith, reverence for their age and grati∣tude


for their kindness, combined with the tender apprehension of losing them, add strength to our former affectionate feelings, and awaken that almost divine enthu∣siasm which inspired Pope's filial prayer:

" Me let the tender office long engage,

" To rock the cradle of declining Age;

" Explore the thought, explain the asking eye,

" And keep awhile a parent from the sky!"
